---
---

<section class="science section" aria-labelledby="science-heading">
  <div class="container science__inner">

    <!-- Left: copy -->
    <div class="science__copy">
      <p class="science__eyebrow">The science</p>
      <h2 class="science__headline" id="science-heading">
        This isn't a trend.<br>It's biology.
      </h2>
      <div class="science__body">
        <p>
          Intermittent fasting triggers measurable metabolic changes —
          not theories, not influencer claims. After 12 hours without food,
          your body begins burning stored fat as its primary fuel.
        </p>
        <p>
          After 16 hours, it enters peak fat-burning mode and begins
          autophagy — the cellular cleanup process recognized by the
          Nobel Prize in 2016.
        </p>
        <p class="science__closer">
          FastMode shows you exactly when these thresholds happen.
          In real time. On your wrist.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="science__source">
        Referenced from Harvard Health Publishing and peer-reviewed
        research on intermittent fasting and metabolic health.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: stats -->
    <aside class="science__stats" aria-label="Key science figures">

      <div class="science__stat">
        <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--burn" aria-label="12 hours">12h</span>
        <span class="science__stat-label">When fat burn begins</span>
      </div>

      <div class="science__stat">
        <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--peak" aria-label="16 hours">16h</span>
        <span class="science__stat-label">Peak fat burn &amp; autophagy kick in</span>
      </div>

      <div class="science__stat science__stat--last">
        <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--nobel" aria-label="Nobel Prize 2016">Nobel<br>2016</span>
        <span class="science__stat-label">Autophagy research awarded the Nobel Prize in Physiology</span>
      </div>

    </aside>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .science {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(var(--space-2xl), 7vw, 96px);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* ── Copy ── */
  .science__eyebrow {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .science__headline {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .science__body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .science__body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 46ch;
  }

  .science__closer {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-primary) !important;
  }

  .science__source {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    max-width: 44ch;
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* ── Stats ── */
  .science__stats {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding-top: 6px;
  }

  .science__stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding-block: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__stat--last {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__stat-value {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    display: block;
  }

  .science__stat-value--burn  { color: var(--color-success); }
  .science__stat-value--peak  { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .science__stat-value--nobel { color: var(--color-text-primary); }

  .science__stat-label {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 28ch;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .science__inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .science__stats {
      flex-direction: row;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    .science__stat {
      flex: 1 1 140px;
      border-top: none;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .science__stat--last {
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .science__stat-value {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3rem);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .science__stats {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .science__stat {
      border-right: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: var(--space-lg) 0;
    }

    .science__stat--last {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
  }
</style>
